  "name": "Morrison CFD Hemolysis Credibility Assessment — CPB Worst-Case Operating Conditions (MRL 2)",
  "description": "Credibility assessment for a steady-state CFD model predicting hemolysis index in the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. The model is used to identify worst-case hemolysis operating points for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. A 13-factor ASME V&V 40 evaluation was conducted; 7 factors were formally assessed and all met required levels, while 6 factors were scoped out as acceptable at MRL 2. The intended use is to support a 510(k) submission by demonstrating that peak hemolysis occurs at the design boundary flow rate of 5 L/min and 3500 RPM, not within the nominal clinical operating envelope. Clinical context, patient population (adult CPB), and device operating envelope are described in the bound requirement and claim documents.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-mrl2-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cpb-cfd-hemolysis-worst-case-claim",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/morrison-fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-hemolysis-bench-measurements-2023"
  ],
