    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cpb-cou1-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-cvsl-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 formally assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2 under the ASME V&V 40 framework. The 6 non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 with documented justification. Output comparison for hemolysis index achieves level 3, providing additional confidence margin. The computational model is accepted as credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump in CPB service for a Class II 510(k) submission. No unresolved weakeners identified.",
